In Unity, physics simulations should be done using FixedUpdate method instead of Update method. The reason for this is that physics calculations are frame rate independent (they're affected by time.fixedDeltaTime, not time.deltaTime), while Update method is affected by frame rate. Therefore, if you use Update for physics calculations, you may experience jittery movement or performance problems in your game.

